The county-by-county face mask rules could soon be replaced by one encompassing all of California.
Gavin Newsom said he is “leaning in that direction.” Face masks have been required in public in Los Angeles since April 10.
Newsom said he and his family wear face masks when shopping for groceries.
He does not wear a face mask when conducting press briefings about face masks.
Official guidance on homemade face masks and their benefits has been inconsistent.